From Mike's pate book-rated excellent

500 grams of finely diced pork shoulder
360g of bacon a pÎ¿rk belly
500 g of sausage
100 g of pork liver
100 g of hazel nuts
3 shallots
2 med onions
half a cup of cognac
parsley
1 tsp of hot paprika
salt and pepper to taste (3/4 Tbsp per pound and 1 tsp per pound)

cut the meat finely along with the hazelnuts, parsley, shallots and onions.

mix in the cognac, salt, pepper and paprika

pack in wide-mouthed jars that have been sterilized

heat in a boiling water bath for at least 2 hours

keeps for up to one month in the fridge
